216
00:20:12,938 --> 00:20:21,603
Heringshaw, if it was something that you didn't think it was, it was condemnable by the city, would that push it over the line or not?

217
00:20:21,683 --> 00:20:29,887
I'm just trying to understand where the line is because I think the previous commissioner had a different line, to be perfectly honest, which is okay.

218
00:20:30,247 --> 00:20:31,408
I'm not questioning your authority.

219
00:20:31,428 --> 00:20:33,429
I'm just trying to understand where that line is for you, sir.

220
00:20:35,107 --> 00:20:42,552
Again, Commissioner car I would say that my, my authority lies only on the imminent threat to public safety.

221
00:20:43,252 --> 00:20:51,317
I would not cite a given example of where I might cite a building unsafe and and order it's order it's demolition.

222
00:20:53,052 --> 00:20:59,415
In a case where a building might be falling apart on a public way, that would be one thing.

223
00:21:00,495 --> 00:21:06,518
Another situation might be that a house is abandoned and open to the weather and in disrepair.

224
00:21:07,318 --> 00:21:08,679
I might order it fenced in.

225
00:21:09,519 --> 00:21:15,882
But in no case do we order a building down unless the threat to public safety is imminent.

226
00:21:15,902 --> 00:21:16,622
And I'll tell you why.

227
00:21:16,682 --> 00:21:20,064
Because insurance companies will cite

228
00:21:23,123 --> 00:21:36,376
you know, the building inspector is going beyond the scope of his authority, especially in cases where there might be a fire investigation or there might be some other reason why a building shouldn't come down right away.

229
00:21:37,297 --> 00:21:41,922
If the building is insured, I assume that the building is not insured at this point.

230
00:21:43,907 --> 00:21:54,392
you know, there would be a conflict of interest with the insurance company, and it would expose the city to liabilities that otherwise may not be covered under Chapter 268A.

231
00:21:55,192 --> 00:21:58,614
And that's why I'm very specific about staying in my lane.

232
00:21:59,615 --> 00:22:10,660
You know, again, if this was a house that was on or near a public way, and you know, the threat was dangerous and imminent, I would essentially, to exercise my authority,

233
00:22:11,511 --> 00:22:15,195
I would actually have to enact what's called a board of survey.

234
00:22:15,215 --> 00:22:29,691
A board of survey is basically the fire chief, myself, and a disinterested party, such as a structural engineer that doesn't work in the city, to do a careful survey of the property to determine whether or not the structure has to come down.

235
00:22:30,012 --> 00:22:32,695
Here's an example of a careful survey.

236
00:22:33,275 --> 00:22:40,700
I actually had a radio tower, a communications tower in Waltham that was 290 feet tall, never had a building permit.

237
00:22:41,181 --> 00:22:43,122
So I could not determine whether or not it was safe.

238
00:22:43,502 --> 00:22:44,543
We performed a survey.

239
00:22:44,683 --> 00:22:47,105
We actually got a court order and had it taken down.

240
00:22:48,065 --> 00:22:52,288
So in cases like that, that's where we would exercise that authority.

241
00:22:53,009 --> 00:22:57,672
But simply opining that a building has to come down is not exactly

242
00:22:58,470 --> 00:23:01,452
within the scope of the authority of the building commissioner.

243
00:23:01,872 --> 00:23:03,093
I can certainly go there.

244
00:23:03,233 --> 00:23:04,034
I can inspect it.

245
00:23:04,194 --> 00:23:08,276
I can cite it as an unsafe structure, but I would stop right there.

246
00:23:08,637 --> 00:23:11,558
Um, I would, you know, it would, it would be removed or make safe.

247
00:23:11,879 --> 00:23:19,984
Um, and so, uh, again, I, I wouldn't want to do anything that would supersede the authority of the commission, um, especially on a historic building.

248
00:23:20,024 --> 00:23:24,787
I've been asked to do it dozens of times in other communities and I refused, um, only because

249
00:23:25,980 --> 00:23:35,243
Um, you know, it undermines, uh, you know, it's, you know, it kind of, um, supersedes the, the authority of the commission to make its determination.

250
00:23:35,363 --> 00:23:43,645
So, um, in short, I don't want to take up too much time, but, but I would just tell you that my philosophy is a little bit more conservative than my predecessor.

